content:
Roll Back a Lambda Update

This feature is available with these telephony models: 
SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH AMAZON CONNECT SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY FROM AMAZON CONNECT SERVICE CLOUD VOICE WITH PARTNER TELEPHONY

In the AWS Management Console, go to the Lambda console. Search for the Lambda that you want to roll back and click the function name. Open the function’s Version tab.

To go back to a previous version of a Service Cloud Voice Lambda, edit the Active Alias. To edit the Lambda version, go to Lambda’s Code section, edit the Configuration, and publish your changes. To save your changes as the newest version, go to the Alias section and set your custom Lambda to Active.
title: Roll Back a Lambda Update in Service Cloud
